This paper deals with sentiment analysis using machine learning techniques and neural networks, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses deep learning techniques such as LSTM and CNN, which are commonly used in the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper deals with creating distributed representations of words and sentences, which is a common topic in the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves information retrieval (cs.IR) as it deals with mining people's opinions from Twitter data. Finally, the paper deals with social networks (cs.SI) as it uses Twitter data for sentiment analysis.
